               <head>Pashto/Pakhto language explained in Persian, Ghunchah-ye Roh</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Ghunchah-'i rūh by Nūr Muḥammad Afghān</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109230 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85074527" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4511-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Grammar and description of the Pashtu language in Persian by Nur Muhammad Afghan residing in Qandahar, consisting of a muqaddimah, two maqṣad, and khātimah </p>
                        <p>Patronised by Amīr al-Muʾminīn Amīr Shīr ʿAlī Khān ibn Dūst Muḥammad Khān Bārakzaʾī (d. 1879), the work was begun 15 Muḥarram 1280 and completed 25 Ṣafar in the same year. The title is the chronogram for the date of completion </p>
                        <p>Not dated </p>
                        <p>Torn and fragile; lacking original covers </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="pas">Persian &amp; Pashtu</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22037">Ghunchah-'i rūh</title>
